tip.text: love the mentaiko pasta!
go for the passionfruit tart! oozing goodness
LOVE THEIR DESSERT! Okay so skip green curry and fried cuttle fish, choose red tom yum over white. Must order the fried omette and beef soup noodles. All dessert were fab
Beautiful interior and good range of pastas. They dont have an english menu but it's okay with the pictures to just point on during ordering. Nothing to pick on, I enjoyed the food and atmosphere

venue.name: 壁の穴 新宿西口店

tip.text: The lunch set that cost only 950 yen which is about sgd12 and is a steal. It was okay, value for money.
Tried the garlic butter and is is indeed finger licking good! we had the combo 1. The seafood is indeed very fresn and mad yummy, just that i find it a little expensive as it wasnt filling for $88++
So first we found hair in the pasta with no apology was made, later the pork ribs was found uncooked and apparently this is acceptable accordingly to the male service manager. horrid guy, asshole svc
The pies are pretty delish, just a little tad dry. I was really surprised how amazing their dessert are instead. Go for the earl grey slice cake if you are a fan of that tea else go for sticky date!
The roasted peanut bingsu is fab! I had the bingsu for 1 which is delicious with the Milky flakes, roasted peanut powder, almond And top with mochi
came for dessert and had their creme brûlée which surprised me with the hint of milk tea. good stuff though i cant say for their dry carrot cake.. on top of tt, service was great.
This is what i call a hidden gem.. there is honestly nothing to complain about, the food, service and ambience are fab👍. enjoy my brunch -  eggs royals and waffles with chicken thigh were perfect.

Had Mentaiko creamy pasta which has not bad, just a pity that the pasta was a overcooked, the honey oat burger was really delish with the chewy buns and fried chicken in btw. A bit pricy but nice food
ambience is great for chilling and chatting till late night

tip.text: only two toast served and both are delicious, Grab a window seat and dont forget to check out their backyard which are fab for phototaking
Sweet potato fries were good and the sauces to go with are excellent. Otherwise, everything else was so so.. The cheese infused cream pasta was overpowering, couldnt go beyond my 4th bite
The cold dishes 凉菜are fab, go for the 东北拉皮、猪肚凉拌，黑木耳，水煮天鸡，口水鸡。Skip the noodles, prepare for brace the crowd and bad service though
